Upon performing balloon dilation again for the stricture measured about 8 mm, we identified that same lacerations were consistently forming only in the 4 o’clock direction. Therefore, we adopted a strategy of performing mucosal incisions prior to balloon dilation to redistribute pressure applied to the stricture site during dilation (
